\section{Results}

\subsection{Oracle-Based Algorithms}

Oracle-based algorithms use quantum oracles to mark solution states and employ amplitude amplification to increase their probabilities.

\subsubsection{Grover's Search Algorithm}

Grover's search demonstrates quadratic speedup for unstructured database search. The algorithm consists of:
\begin{enumerate}
	\item Initialize qubits to $|0\rangle^{\otimes n}$
	\item Apply Hadamard gates for uniform superposition
	\item Repeat $O(\sqrt{N})$ times:
	      \begin{itemize}
		      \item Oracle: Phase flip on target state
		      \item Diffusion: Amplitude amplification
	      \end{itemize}
	\item Measure to obtain solution
\end{enumerate}

Figure \ref{fig:grover_comparison} shows the visualization comparison for Grover's algorithm.

