	\caption{Comparison of visualization techniques for Grover's search algorithm with $n=2$ qubits:
		(a) Bloch sphere showing geometric rotation of state vector from initial superposition
		toward target state $|11\rangle$ after two iterations;
		(b) State City density matrix revealing probability amplification from 0.25 to 1.0;
		(c) Quantum circuit diagram showing Oracle and Diffusion operators;
