		Bloch Sphere           & Low                    & Cannot show multi-qubit phases \\
		State City             & High                   & Phase periodicity visible      \\
		Circuit Diagram        & High                   & Butterfly pattern visible      \\ \bottomrule
	\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\subsection{Variational Algorithms}

Variational algorithms combine quantum circuits with classical optimization to solve optimization problems.

\subsubsection{QAOA (Quantum Approximate Optimization Algorithm)}

QAOA solves combinatorial optimization problems by varying parameters $\gamma$ and $\beta$:

\begin{equation}
	|\psi(\gamma, \beta)\rangle = U(\beta) U(\gamma) |+\rangle^{\otimes n}
\end{equation}

Figure \ref{fig:qaoa_comparison} shows the visualization comparison.

\begin{figure}[h!]
	\centering
	\caption{QAOA: Visualization Comparison}
	\label{fig:qaoa_comparison}
	\fbox{\includegraphics[width=0.9\textwidth]{figures/qaoa_stages_combined.png}}
\end{figure}

\textbf{Key Findings:}

\begin{itemize}
	\item \textbf{Bloch Sphere} provides limited value (doesn't show optimization)
	\item \textbf{State City} shows solution probability improvement
	\item \textbf{Cost Landscape} reveals the optimization surface with minima
	\item \textbf{Circuit Diagram} shows ansatz structure (problem + mixer layers)
\end{itemize}

\begin{table}[h!]
	\centering
	\caption{Visualization Effectiveness for QAOA}
	\label{tab:qaoa_visualization}
	\begin{tabular}{@{}lll@{}}
		\toprule
		\textbf{Visualization} & \textbf{Insight Level} & \textbf{Unique Value}           \\ \midrule
		Bloch Sphere           & Low                    & No parameter optimization shown \\
		State City             & Medium                 & Solution quality visible        \\
		Cost Landscape         & High                   & Optimization surface visible    \\
		Circuit Diagram        & High                   & Ansatz structure visible        \\ \bottomrule
	\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\subsubsection{VQE (Variational Quantum Eigensolver)}

VQE finds ground state energies by minimizing the expectation value $E(\theta) = \langle\psi(\theta)|H|\psi(\theta)\rangle$.

\textbf{Key Findings:}

\begin{itemize}
	\item \textbf{Energy Landscape} shows minimization trajectory toward ground state
	\item State City demonstrates amplitude shift toward ground state basis states
	\item Circuit Diagram reveals hardware-efficient ansatz structure
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Simulation-Based Algorithms}

Simulation-based algorithms emulate quantum system dynamics under Hamiltonians.

\subsubsection{Rabi Oscillation}

Rabi oscillation demonstrates coherent population transfer between quantum states under resonant driving:

\begin{equation}
	|\psi(t)\rangle = \cos(\Omega t)|0\rangle - i\sin(\Omega t)|1\rangle
\end{equation}

Figure \ref{fig:simulation_comparison} shows the visualization comparison.

\begin{figure}[h!]
	\centering
	\caption{Rabi Oscillation: Trajectory Visualization}
	\label{fig:simulation_comparison}
	\fbox{\includegraphics[width=0.9\textwidth]{figures/rabi_trajectory_combined.png}}
\end{figure}

\textbf{Key Findings:}

\begin{itemize}
	\item \textbf{Bloch Sphere Trajectory} shows the state vector rotating on the sphere surface
	\item \textbf{Dynamic Flow} reveals time evolution through multiple time points
	\item Z vs Time plot quantifies the oscillation period
\end{itemize}

\begin{table}[h!]
